<section class="section section--compact" id="qec-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure">
      <strong>This is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor reference &mdash; not Intuit, and not QuickBooks&rsquo; official support.</strong> For Intuit software-level issues (login, billing, subscription, license validation), Intuit&rsquo;s own support is the right path. We provide independent, operational help resolving errors inside QuickBooks files. QuickBooks and Intuit are registered trademarks of Intuit Inc.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="qec-credentials">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Certified by Intuit &middot; Desktop &amp; Enterprise specialists</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stat-row">
      {%- for s in credStats %}
      <div><div class="stat__value">{{ s.value }}</div><div class="stat__label">{{ s.label }}</div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qec-tldr">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">QuickBooks error codes, plainly.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="qec-tldr-body">QuickBooks errors fall into <strong>six recognizable families</strong>: <strong>H-series</strong> (H101, H202, H505 &mdash; multi-user and network connectivity), <strong>6000-series</strong> (6000-77, 6000-301, 6189, 6190 &mdash; file access and integrity), <strong>PS-series</strong> (PS032, PS036, PS038 &mdash; payroll subscription and tax tables), <strong>3000- and 80000-series</strong> (3371, 80070057 &mdash; license validation and file path), <strong>15000-series</strong> (15215, 15240 &mdash; payroll updates and maintenance), and <strong>unrecoverable / C-series</strong> (file corruption and critical faults). The codes in this reference apply almost entirely to <strong>QuickBooks Desktop, Premier, Mac, and Enterprise</strong>; <a href="/quickbooks/online/">QuickBooks Online</a> uses descriptive text messages rather than numbered codes. The honest read: many first-occurrence errors resolve with documented self-fix steps (QuickBooks Tool Hub, firewall checks, configuration adjustments) &mdash; the dedicated page for each code walks you through them. But errors that <strong>recur, cluster, involve file corruption, or block critical work</strong> typically require a <a href="/quickbooks/cleanup/">Certified ProAdvisor&rsquo;s file repair</a>, scoped as fixed-fee work after a 30-minute diagnostic. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qec-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks error codes, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qec-families">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The six error families</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Find your error&rsquo;s family.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Most QuickBooks errors fall into one of these six families. Identify your code&rsquo;s family, then scan the specific codes below. If your error isn&rsquo;t resolving, a <a href="/contact/?intent=qb-error">ProAdvisor diagnostic</a> identifies the real cause.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for f in families %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="review-card__role">{{ f.codes }}</p>
        <h3>{{ f.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ f.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qec-h-series">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">H-series</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Multi-user mode &amp; network errors.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">H-series errors share a root: QuickBooks is configured for multi-user but a workstation can&rsquo;t reach the company file on the host. The specific code narrows where in that chain the problem is.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for c in hSeries %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{% if c.href %}<a href="{{ c.href }}">{{ c.name | safe }}</a>{% else %}{{ c.name | safe }}{% endif %}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qec-6000-series">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">6000-series</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">File access &amp; integrity errors.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">6000-series errors involve the company file itself &mdash; whether QuickBooks can open it, whether it&rsquo;s locked, whether it&rsquo;s damaged, or whether permissions are correct. <a href="/quickbooks/help/error-codes/error-6000-series/">The complete 6000-series overview</a> covers every variant.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for c in sixThousand %}
