<section class="section section--alt" id="qec-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How we resolve QuickBooks errors</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Diagnostic, then fixed-fee fix.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every error-driven engagement starts with a 30-minute diagnostic. We identify the actual root cause, then scope the fix in writing &mdash; fixed-fee, no hourly billing, before any work begins.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">0{{ loop.index }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qec-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who diagnoses your error</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified ProAdvisors who&rsquo;ve seen this code before.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Error codes look intimidating because they&rsquo;re cryptic by design &mdash; QuickBooks doesn&rsquo;t explain what H202 or PS038 actually means. But every error in this reference has been resolved many times over by Certified ProAdvisors. The diagnostic isn&rsquo;t guesswork; it&rsquo;s pattern recognition &mdash; matching the code, its context, and the file&rsquo;s state against errors already solved.</p>
      <p>Every TechBrot operator holds active Certified ProAdvisor credentials across Desktop, Enterprise, Online (Level 2), and Payroll, verifiable on Intuit&rsquo;s public ProAdvisor directory. We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription &mdash; so the recommendation you get is what fixes your error, not what bills more. You can <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">meet the ProAdvisor team</a> or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qec-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
